// Cross-cutting (regulation sits deep — every regulated component "depends on" it)
component Space Regulation [0.10, 0.42]

// Dependencies — user → access
Consumers->Network Access
Consumers->Broadcast
Corporations->Network Access
Corporations->Physical Network
Government->Network Access
Government->Physical Network
Government->Broadcast

// Access → topology
Network Access->Mobile Topology
Network Access->Fibre Topology
Network Access->Non-Terrestrial Networks
Physical Network->Mobile Topology
Physical Network->Fibre Topology
Physical Network->Non-Terrestrial Networks
Broadcast->Non-Terrestrial Networks

// Topology → space stack
Non-Terrestrial Networks->User Terminals
Non-Terrestrial Networks->Ground Stations
Non-Terrestrial Networks->Spectrum Ku/Ka
Non-Terrestrial Networks->Spectrum V-band
User Terminals->Phased-Array Antennas
User Terminals->Spectrum Ku/Ka
Ground Stations->Spectrum Ku/Ka

// Space stack → satellites
User Terminals->LEO Microsat
User Terminals->GEO Satellite
Ground Stations->LEO Microsat
Ground Stations->GEO Satellite
Phased-Array Antennas->Beamforming
Phased-Array Antennas->Beam-Steering

// Satellites → subsystems
LEO Microsat->Satellite Antennas
LEO Microsat->Optical Sat-to-Sat Comms
LEO Microsat->Power Subsystem
LEO Microsat->Thermal Electric Cooling
LEO Microsat->Krypton Propulsion
LEO Microsat->Xenon Propulsion
GEO Satellite->Satellite Antennas
GEO Satellite->Power Subsystem
GEO Satellite->Radiative Cooling
GEO Satellite->Cryogenic Cooling
GEO Satellite->Xenon Propulsion
Satellite Antennas->Beamforming
Satellite Antennas->Beam-Steering

// Satellites → launch and ops
LEO Microsat->Launchers
GEO Satellite->Launchers
LEO Microsat->Fleet Management
GEO Satellite->Fleet Management
Fleet Management->Orbit Tracking
Fleet Management->Debris Tracking
Fleet Management->Constellation Automation
Launchers->Supply-Chain Awareness
LEO Microsat->Supply-Chain Awareness

// Cross-cutting regulation (touches multiple layers)
Non-Terrestrial Networks->Space Regulation
Spectrum Ku/Ka->Space Regulation
Spectrum V-band->Space Regulation
Launchers->Space Regulation
Debris Tracking->Space Regulation

// Evolution movements (scenario, not forecast — Feb 2023 signals)
evolve Non-Terrestrial Networks 0.55
evolve Phased-Array Antennas 0.70
evolve Optical Sat-to-Sat Comms 0.50
evolve Krypton Propulsion 0.55
